This paper is about unsupervised machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of neural networks and optimization techniques, which are common in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of cross-lingual embeddings, which are often used in neural network-based NLP tasks such as machine translation and sentiment analysis. This could potentially place the paper in the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE) or computer vision (cs.CV), which also make use of embeddings.
